We don&#39;t know anything more about optimal values of this parameter than 
what&#39;s the in the Oracle documentation.

25 was chosen as the initial value because that&#39;s the number of 
ToeThreads in our example configurations, and it&#39;s possible that all 
ToeThreads could be doing BDB operations at once.

Most crawls will have that number of maximum ToeThreads or more, but 
whether its strictly necessary to also increase expectedConcurrency when 
there&#39;s a chance of more concurrent BDB operations is not clear.

No testing of alternate values has occurred, and none is planned unless 
BDB locks show up in other thread reports/profiling as a performance 
bottleneck. (Thus far, it hasn&#39;t.)

- Gordon @ IA

